		{
			dependencies: ["7703F0CA1A8AB6F9"]
			description: [
				"A &6&oshaft&r&r can be used to connect two mechanical components such that the rotation of one rotates the other."
				""
				"When two mechanical components are connected to each other by a shaft, any &2rotational force&r provided to either component will be provided to the other component in addition to that &dspeed&r. As such, if both components provide stress, this can cause the machine to become overstressed."
			]
			id: "0E5FC39E6C71A872"
			rewards: [
				{
					count: 8
					id: "63F1F642BA66A01F"
					item: "create:shaft"
					type: "item"
				}
				{
					id: "481C95D840F84CF9"
					type: "xp"
					xp: 100
				}
			]
			shape: "gear"
			size: 1.75d
			subtitle: "The shaft is a basic mechanical component in Create. "
			tasks: [{
				id: "0B967F9E0B8B2BB6"
				item: "create:shaft"
				type: "item"
			}]
			title: "&l&6Shaft"
			x: -2.5d
			y: 3.5d
		}
		{
			dependencies: ["7703F0CA1A8AB6F9"]
			description: [
				"Casings are blocks used throughout many crafting recipes in Create, as well as for decoration and aesthetic purposes."
				""
				"There are four types of Casings: Andesite Casings are mainly used in basic &3Contraptions&r."
				""
				"Casings can only be crafted through physically applying a valid alloy or ingot to any Stripped variant of Log or Wood. The logs will convert themselves into the casing."
				""
				"Mechanical Belts, Shafts, and Cogwheels can be encased in most casings, creating a decoration around the encased block. Copper casings, however, can be used only on Fluid Pipes. Likewise, a fluid pipe will not accept any other kind of casing."
			]
			id: "4B976C143EDA4317"
			rewards: [
				{
					id: "7E9FCF31726AC080"
					type: "xp"
					xp: 100
