		{
			dependencies: [
				"5AFD4912CC8FBBB8"
				"0EE2E9EB6DC01E34"
			]
			description: [
				"&6Trains&r are &3&3Contraptions&r&r that travel on Train Tracks."
				""
				"Assembly"
				"1) Place the track and right-click it with a station block. Place the station block near the track."
				""
				"2) Right click on the station and select \"Create Train\" to enter assembly mode (blue flag shown on station)."
				""
				"3) Place one or more Train Casings on the track where indicated with blue. The casings will turn into bogeys."
				""
				"4) When assembled, each bogey will automatically become coupled together as part of the train."
				" "
				"5) Place a Train Controls block facing the direction dictated by the station. Place a Seat or Blaze Burner behind the controls for the driver."
				""
				"6) Use Block Attachment Utilities such as Super Glue to connect all parts together (green highlight)."
				""
				"7) When finished, use the Station's interface to attempt to assemble the Train. If a Train fails to assemble, an error will be shown in the Station's interface. Common errors are detailed below."
			]
			id: "147FC2959F9FC5F5"
			rewards: [{
				exclude_from_claim_all: true
				id: "3B3DC79DB3261E5C"
				type: "random"
			}]
			shape: "gear"
			size: 1.5d
			subtitle: "Train Casings are used for locomotive transportation."
