		{
			dependencies: ["4BB13C80196FD034"]
			description: [
				"Super Glue has two ways to be used: Block by Block Mode and Area Mode. You can mix both methods on the same contraption."
				""
				"Every time you use the glue, it loses one durability point. You can enchant it with Unbreaking and Mending to make it last longer."
				""
				"In Block by Block Mode, the glue works like a Slimeball. Right-clicking a Linear or Radial Chassis applies glue to one face, letting you attach other blocks. To remove the glue from a chassis, sneak and right-click with an empty hand."
				""
				"In Area Mode, you can glue a group of blocks that are already placed. Start by right-clicking one corner of the section, then move to the opposite corner. A green box will show the selected area. Right-click again to glue the blocks. If you want to cancel, sneak and right-click. The second corner can be up to 24 blocks away, and the total volume can be up to 2312 blocks. No matter how big the selection is, it only uses one durability point. Overlapping glued areas will merge while keeping their shape. You can’t select the face of a chassis in Area Mode—it will switch to Block by Block Mode instead. To avoid this, click the side of the chassis instead."
			]
			id: "35C37231C1C86294"
